---
// On Me — bio with synesthesia hover-coloring on selected words.
---
<section class="section on-me" id="on-me" data-section-id="on-me">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 data-color-letters data-inertial-text>on me</h2>
    <div class="bio">
      <p class="bio-lead">
        As a student beginning in <strong>Computer Science</strong>, one thing I can say in
        <em>high confidence</em>:
        <span data-syn-word>massive change</span> is not only imminent but in fast motion.
      </p>
      <p>
        In that change, people can, like much other change, push towards a
        <span data-syn-word>better world</span> or break it down as we know it. For me, that
        makes my goal discovering the fields I am most interested in and joining initiatives
        utilizing this program to participate in <span data-syn-word>meaningful</span>
        endeavors, build things, or simply message <span data-syn-word>Claude Code</span>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .on-me .bio {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 38rem;
  }

  .on-me .bio p {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--face-text);
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 0.35vw + 0.98rem, 1.12rem);
    line-height: 1.72;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    color: var(--text-1);
  }

  .on-me .bio-lead {
    font-family: var(--face-display);
    font-variation-settings: 'SOFT' 75, 'WONK' 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.08rem, 0.45vw + 1rem, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-0);
  }

  .on-me .bio strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-0);
  }

  .on-me .bio em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-variation-settings: 'SOFT' 90;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text-0) 88%, var(--accent));
  }

  :root[data-theme="dark"] .on-me {
    background-color: rgb(
      calc(20 + var(--syn-r, 200) * 0.06),
      calc(18 + var(--syn-g, 180) * 0.06),
      calc(16 + var(--syn-b, 160) * 0.06)
    );
    transition: background-color 1.2s ease;
  }
  :root[data-theme="dark"] .on-me.syn-tinted {
    background-color: rgb(
      calc(30 + var(--syn-r) * 0.22),
      calc(27 + var(--syn-g) * 0.22),
      calc(24 + var(--syn-b) * 0.22)
    );
  }
</style>
